# GLOW_PROFILE.bron — this contributor's professional profile.
#
# Copy this file to GLOW_PROFILE.bron at the repository root and fill in YOUR
# values. GLOW_PROFILE.bron is gitignored (personal identity metadata); only
# this .template is committed, so it works for anyone who clones the fork.
#
# Why this file exists. Glow OS's reader-facing docs address a generic Acme
# Corporation employee, never a named individual (see
# .cursor/rules/acme-employee-voice.mdc). That keeps the tree shareable and
# teachable. But some things a real contributor genuinely needs are specific
# and professional: the real name that signs the work, forge handles, the
# clock stamps come from, the editor and voice defaults for session logs.
# Rather than scatter those specifics through the generic docs, they live
# here, in one loadable Bron profile — the sibling, in Bron, to GLOW_HOST.bron
# (which declares the host and toolchain) and to .claude/rules / .cursor/rules
# (which configure agent behavior). This one declares the contributor.
#
# Single source of truth: canonical public fingerprints live in PUBKEYS.md,
# not here — this file points at that record rather than copying it, per
# context/TAME_GUIDANCE.md root rule 9 (docs and implementation stay synced).

format glow-profile-v1

# --- Identity — the professional "who" that signs this work -----------------
# Use your real professional name; this is the name a paid contribution ships
# under. The generic docs never say it — this file is where it lives.
name Your Full Name
handle_github your-github-handle
handle_codeberg your-codeberg-handle
email you@example.com

# --- Signing — pointer, not a copy ------------------------------------------
# Canonical SSH + OpenPGP fingerprints live in PUBKEYS.md (or context/PUBKEYS.md).
# This points there so the two never drift apart.
pubkeys PUBKEYS.md

# --- Urbit Azimuth points (optional) ----------------------------------------
# If you hold real Azimuth points, name them here. Per the placeholder-ship-names
# rule, real points are NEVER used as example ship names in generic docs — only
# named in identity records like this one. Leave blank if you hold none yet.
azimuth_star
azimuth_planet

# --- Clock — where your stamps come from ------------------------------------
# The one-clock naming law takes stamps from the contributor verbatim; this
# names which wall clock that is, so a reader knows how to read your stamps.
# Each host may seat its own convention (e.g. Pacific on a macOS clone,
# UDT/UTC on the Framework Ubuntu host after 20260720.232932) — see
# context/specs/ for host notes. Pick the IANA zone your system clock uses.
timezone Etc/UTC
timezone_label UDT (UTC)

# --- Session-log defaults for this clone ------------------------------------
# The session-logs rule reads these as the default editor/model/voice for logs
# written from this clone. Record the model that actually produces each log;
# update this field when the clone switches models. Standing voice is Quin
# (Reya 2 · Rio 3 · Riyo rest retired in context/archive/).
editor Cursor
model Cursor Grok 4.5 300k High Fast
voice Quin

# --- Placeholder identities for examples ------------------------------------
# Structurally-invalid @p placeholders for docs and commands (never a real
# point). See .cursor/rules/placeholder-ship-names.mdc for the full table.
placeholder_galaxy ~acme
placeholder_star ~acme-star
placeholder_planet ~acme-corp-test-ship

# --- When this profile was last confirmed correct (your local stamp) --------
checked YYYYMMDD.HHMMSS
